The paper deals with distributed representations of distances in metric spaces, which is a topic closely related to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of distance labeling and $\ell_\infty$-embeddings, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The prioritized versions of these measures involve ranking and ordering, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and social networks (cs.SI).
